{"to":["requestor@example.com"],"subject":"Latest Candidate Assessment Links & Summary","body":"Hi [Your Name],

All active candidate assessment pages have just been refreshed in Notion. You can find them in the Talent Acquisition workspace → “Active Candidates” database. Direct links are listed below along with a concise snapshot for each person:

1. Michael Turner – Overall assessment: Strong hire (4.5/5)
   • Strengths: Robust Python & Java expertise, methodical problem-solving, proactive communication.
   • Development areas: Broader exposure to front-end frameworks.
   • Interview panel highlights: Consistently positive technical interview performance; strong culture-add impressions from peer panel.
   • Outstanding follow-ups / next steps: Schedule final leadership interview and begin reference checks.

2. Jennifer O’Brien – Overall assessment: Hire (4/5)
   • Strengths: Cloud infrastructure design, mentoring junior engineers.
   • Development areas: Needs deeper experience with large-scale data pipelines.
   • Interview panel highlights: Architectural whiteboard session praised; pair-programming solid.
   • Outstanding follow-ups / next steps: Provide take-home system-design exercise.

3. Ravi Desai – Overall assessment: Hold / needs more data (3.2/5)
   • Strengths: Low-level performance optimization, C++ expertise.
   • Development areas: Communication brevity; stakeholder alignment.
   • Interview panel highlights: Mixed feedback – excellent coding but presentation slightly unfocused.
   • Outstanding follow-ups / next steps: Schedule supplemental behavioral interview.

Feel free to dive into the individual pages for full scorecards, panel comments, and detailed rationale. Let me know if you’d like anything else or a different format.

Best,
Jane","cc":null,"bcc":null,"execution_log_path":"data/logs/item32_execution_log.json","card_path":"data/agent_cards/item32_recipient.json"}
